# Chrome MV3 extension conventions

Applies to: `src/`, `manifest.json`, `dist/`

## Architecture

- UI layers (`popup/`, `options/`) call **shared** storage and types only.
- **Background** service worker owns DNR sync — UI never calls `declarativeNetRequest` directly.
- Rule shape is defined once in `src/shared/types.ts`.

## Permissions

- Request least privilege per slice; document each permission in manifest comments or docs.
- Do not log header values or tokens.
- Avoid blocking `webRequest`; use `declarativeNetRequest.modifyHeaders`.

## URL matching

- Supported patterns: exact origin (`https://example.com`, `example.com`) and subdomain wildcard (`*.example.com`, `*example.com`).
- Any change to matching logic requires tests in `tests/url-match.test.ts`.

## Storage

- Use `chrome.storage.local` via `src/shared/storage.ts`.
- Treat stored header values as sensitive on shared machines.

## Build

- Output goes to `dist/` — load unpacked from there, not repo root.
- Run `make check` (Docker) before marking a slice done.
- Do not run npm on the host; use `make` or `docker compose run --rm dev …`.
